➜China Moves to Cool Real Estate Market
http://www.sohu.com/a/410882002_116132	6960
<p><img src="http://p1.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20200801/3f6e812e42474107ae40fac9a4565bc4.jpeg" /></p>
<p>Credit: Unsplash</p>
<p>BEIJING, July 31 (TMTPOST) –- After the coronavirus outbreak in late January, condo sale offices in all Chinese cities were shut down. Many market observers forecast a decline in sales and profits for 2020.</p>
<p>At least 12 cities in China, including Guangzhou, Baoji, Jinan, Qingdao and Huaian, lessened the restrictions on the qualifications of a property buyer to save a market crash wrecked by the coronavirus. By May it was already a seller’s market due to loose monetary policies and the release of the pent-up demand in the wake of the subdued epidemic in April.</p>
<p>The sale of 959 condos of the Yuanyang Xixi Mansion building in Hangzhou attracted over 60,000 eager buyers in June to register for a lottery for the right to purchase, implying that about 1.6% of those registered will end up being able to buy.</p>
<p>The craziness in Hangzhou property markets was soon beat by Chengdu. A total of 58,177 potential buyers scrambled for 774 units in a new condo building in Longquanyi District in late July, representing a winning rate of 1.3%. A number of other buildings in the southwestern Chinese city also witnessed varying degrees of buyers’ frenzy, according to local media.</p>
<p>It was the first time for Chengdu, the capital of Sichuan province, to see a seller’s market since 2018 as its relatively low housing prices lured buyers to flock in from other cities. Sales from March to June in 2020 were up 30.9% from the same period of 2019.</p>
<p>In the southern Chinese coastal city of Shenzhen, 44,000 existing condo units were sold in the first half of 2020, up 41% year over year, according to Leyoujia.com. Many new condo buildings witnessed a winning rate of less than 1% in lotteries for the purchase right.</p>
<p>Such frenzy has spilled over to other cities, including but not limited to Nanjing, Dongguan, Ningbo and Changsha.</p>
<p>In Nanjing, the sales of land lots hit RMB 76.085 billion (about US$10.9 billion) in the first six months this year, up 30.98% from the same period of 2019.</p>
<p>In China, all urban land belongs to the government and most local governments rely on land sales for fiscal revenues.</p>
<p>In terms of land sales for property development in China, January and February saw a significant fall. However, due to soaring sales in May and June, the total area of land sold in the first half of 2020 reached 79.65 million square meters, down only 0.9% from the same period of 2019. Land prices in the first six months of 2020 went up 6.8% year over year, according to the E-House Real Estate Research Institute.</p>
<p>In terms of condo sales, 69,400 square meters of office and residential properties were sold in the first half of 2020, representing a year-over-year decline of 8.4%. However, the average sold price for residential properties was up 5.3% year over year while office buildings saw a decline in the average sold price. In the first half of 2020, personal mortgage loans climbed 3.1% year over year.</p>
<p>The official data showed that condo sales rebounded fast in the second quarter following a fall in the first quarter of 2020.</p>
<p><img src="http://p1.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20200801/6ebd3c65f00642348fde00cd684e0484.jpeg" /></p>
<p>Credit: Unsplash</p>
<p><strong>Drastic Steps to Curb Speculation </strong></p>
<p>On July 24, Chinese Deputy Premier Han Zheng cautioned against “housing speculation” and called for “stable land prices, stable housing prices and stable expectations” in a national meeting attended by government officials and bank managers from 10 major cities.</p>
<p>On the following day, the Dongguan municipal government in southern China introduced measures, requiring a first-time home buyer to produce proof of at least one year of work in the city and a second property buyer to produce the proof of two years of work. Buyers already with two properties are prohibited from buying any new condos.</p>
<p>The restrictions mark the second time in July for the Dongguan government to move to cool the market. In earlier July, local housing authorities placed certain restrictions on new condo projects applying for permission for sales, including a price limit.</p>
<p>In Nanjing, the municipal government unveiled new rules, requiring divorced persons to wait for two years before they buy a condo. That closed the legal loophole that some couples divorced in order to gain the right to buy one more condo given the limit of one condo for one family regardless of their size. The majority of such divorced couples would resume their previous marriage after managing to buy one more condo.</p>
<p>Soaring condo prices in the past three decades make Chinese residents assume that buying is tantamount to making money.</p>
<p>Hangzhou has enacted a by-law that buyers with permanent residence registration (aka Hukou) must account for at least 50% of all buyers. Ningbo and Nanjing have also introduced similar measures favourable to local dwellers, as opposed to investment property speculators.</p>
<p>In Shenzhen, mere Hukou does not automatically grant local dwellers the right to buy. The buyer also needs the proof of over a year of employment.</p>
<p>Since 2017, many municipal governments across China have adopted university graduate-friendly Hukou policies to lure the educated young people to relocate to their cities and contribute to local economies. It had also bolstered local property markets until the outbreak of the coronavirus this year.</p>
<p><strong>Balance Between Curbing Speculation and Propping up Economic Growth</strong></p>
<p>The effect of the restrictive measures on buyers showed quickly. In Shenzhen, many property sale offices saw viewer traffic dwindling in late July because many potential buyers lost their status of a qualified shopper.</p>
<p>“The sale offices in Guangming District no longer see a hustle and bustle,” a sales manager said.</p>
<p>“Although the policy has culled the speculators, it has also barred young people who just moved to Shenzhen from buying a home.”</p>
<p>It has been a dilemma in the past three decades. While the restrictive by-laws cracked down the speculators, it also cooled the market and thus slowed down economic growth.</p>
<p>“There is never an easy balance to curb speculation and drive economic growth at the same time,” an unnamed local official told TMT. </p>
<p><strong>更多精彩内容，关注钛媒体微信号（ID：taimeiti），或者下载钛媒体App</strong></p>
➜电竞屏、还有体感， 腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S又耍新花招
http://www.sohu.com/a/410882015_116132	7514
<p><img src="http://p1.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20200801/531594a259b0404eac28c1fec3fc0073.jpeg" /></p>
<blockquote>
<p>文丨竞核</p>
</blockquote>
<p>速度与激情，这是手机硬核派的宣言。</p>
<p>7月31日下午，黑鲨科技正式发布腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S。这距离推出黑鲨游戏手机3 Pro，仅仅不到5个月。迭代速度之快，这很互联网。</p>
<p>该款手机采用三星AMOLED屏，搭载全新的JOYUI 12操作系统，力图为玩家带来畅快的游戏体验。</p>
<p><strong>电竞屏，触控率刷新上限</strong></p>
<p>想必玩家们体验游戏，尤其是FPS射击游戏时经常会遇到点击屏幕，反应滞后的问题。</p>
<p>这与手机屏幕刷新率息息相关。</p>
<p>自黑鲨2首创多指240Hz屏幕触控采样率以来，黑鲨科技一直在努力打磨。本次腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S搭载6.67英寸三星AMOLED屏，屏幕刷新率高达120Hz。</p>
<p>与此同时，触控报点率达到270Hz。这意味着，玩家能够在射击时快人一步。对于热门射击游戏的玩家，爽感将大幅提升。</p>
<p>基于AI智能场景分析，腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S还能实时匹配。外加上腾讯SolarCore3.0游戏引擎，手机终端跟游戏协调性进一步提升。</p>
<p>截至目前，腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S上多款产品已能实现120Hz高帧率模式，比如《QQ飞车》、《CFM》、《王牌战士》等。</p>
<p>可以想见，未来将会有更多游戏产品加入高帧率模式。</p>
<p>至于触控延迟，腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S延时低至17ms。相较于黑鲨3 Pro而言，提升了30%。</p>
<p>玩家还可自定义触控参数。</p>
<p>如果玩家一直玩，终端厂商当然有义务让玩家一直爽。</p>
<p>保护玩家眼睛自然成了头等大事。本次，腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S采用DC调光，能够有效减少OLED屏的频闪问题。</p>
<p><strong>发烫，这是不可能的</strong></p>
<p>玩家对手机性能提出高要求，玩得畅快只是一方面，舒适度还得有所保证。</p>
<p>从诞生初始，黑鲨便一直专注于散热问题。起初采用的多级直触液冷散热解决方案，而后再到二代的双液冷系统，如今已进化至第三代的液冷板加液冷管热源分区。</p>
<p><img src="http://p4.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20200801/3af7118793164ae7a4da549d033ff8f4.png" width="832" height="554" /></p>
<p>腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S进一步进行升级，采用了独特的“三明治”液冷散热系统，两根热管上下两面直触主板热源，360°向外导热。麻麻再也不用担心手机可以发烫煮蛋了。</p>
<p>据官方介绍，新的液冷散热系统能够让关键热源散热面积提升100%，散热能力提升了50%。</p>
<p>鉴于腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S采用中轴式主板散热架构的设计，热源分布距离提升了2倍，有效解决了发烫问题。</p>
<p>可以这么说，在有效散热的同时，保证了玩家的游戏手感。</p>
<p>诚如大家所知，高耗能发烫与手机硬件配置息息相关。</p>
<p>腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S搭载高通骁龙865处理器。相较于前代产品，CPU性能提升25%， GPU渲染性能提升25%。与此同时，得益于AI引擎，算力能够提升100%。</p>
<p>内存方面，腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S标配12G LPDDR5内存，读写带宽提升近50%，功耗降低近20%。</p>
<p><strong>One more thing</strong></p>
<p>体感操作也来了。</p>
<p>玩家们大多在主机上体验过体验。如今手机上也能指尖畅玩了。腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S的体感操控功能支持左、右翻转、前、后翻转、左上、右上倾斜六种体感手势。</p>
<p><img src="http://p3.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20200801/46c649f217a64acc8873c0f7167a4dab.png" width="832" height="554" /></p>
<p>如果玩家有自己的操作系统，当然也可以进行自定义设置。至于双区屏幕压感功能、语音操控功能，腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S全都有，可谓诚意满满。</p>
<p>据悉，语音识别准确率得到大幅提升，玩家还可自定义语音词汇。</p>
<p>续航能力方面，腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S内置一块4720mAh大电池。腾讯黑鲨游戏手机3S有天云黑与水晶蓝两种配色。</p>
<p>售价方面，12GB+128GB 3999元；12GB+256GB 4299元；12GB+512GB版本售价为4799元。</p>
